bug.short_desc: Virtual Table and rowSpan: is not transparent for decoration

long_desc.thetext:
Reported by Marcel Ruff:
I have a virtual Table (qx.ui.virtual.layer.WidgetCellSpan) with a Atom and 48x48 icon with transparent background as a CellWidget.
If I apply a cellWidget.setDecorator("table-scroller-header"); it is nicely displayed on normal cells, but NOT on the cell which is a colSpan.
I'm not able to reproduce this issue. Can you be a bit more specifc about your setup? Maybe with a screenshot or a small code sippet.

Here is a screenshot: http://watchee.net/qooxdoo-decoration-missing.png Each block is of two rows (upper and lower). The second column spans both rows (the caffeine icon) Each cell at the bottom row has widget.setDecorator("table-scroller-header");
But now I know the problem: The caffeine icon is only known at the upper row so the decorator applied at the lower row has no effect.
I have now attach to the coffeine icon at the upper row the decorator and it is displayed!
But: The layout is now ugly as the grey is higher than in the cells left and right: http://watchee.net/qooxdoo-decoration-doublerow.png
A solution could be if it is possible to attach the decorator only to the lower cell, any idea?

Now I get it :-) If I understand you correctly you want to have the “table-scroller-header” decorator as background for the whole row and you cannot set it for the lower part of the coffee icon.
With the WidgetCellSpan layer you simply cannot do it. There you can only set the decorator of whole widgets.
However there is a simple solution to this problem. You can add an additional "Row" layer to your table. The row layer is able to render the background of rows using decorators <http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/demobrowser/#virtual~Pane_Row.html>.
Please reopen the bug if necessary.
Closed all bugs already shipped with a release.
